<h2 id="lets-get-started">Letâ€™s Get Started</h2>
<p>First, we need to create a bucket that will host our static site. Head over to the Amazon S3 and create a bucket like so:</p>

<p><img src="/images/2020-07-10/create-bucket.png" alt="_config.yml" /></p>

<p>For simplicity of this tutorial, go ahead and uncheck â€œBlock all public accessâ€. You should see a banner popup that makes you confirm this action. This is going to make this bucket publicly accessible (this is needed so we can make the files weâ€™ll upload later on available).</p>

<p><img src="/images/2020-07-10/ack-public-access.png" alt="_config.yml" /></p>

<p>Once your bucket is created, we want our bucket to host our static website.
To set that up, navigate over to â€œPropertiesâ€ -&gt; â€œStatic website hostingâ€ -&gt; and check â€œUse this bucket to host a websiteâ€. A few fields will popup asking which HTML files to use and weâ€™ll just stick with the defaults.</p>

<p><img src="/images/2020-07-10/enable-static-hosting.png" alt="_config.yml" /></p>

<p>Now we need to upload the actual <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">index.html</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">error.html</code> files. You can find those <a href="">here</a> or just copy/paste the contents down below:</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;!-- index.html --&gt;
&lt;script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.0.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-migrate-1.2.1.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is index.html&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;br&gt;
    &lt;h3&gt;This is the rest of the page&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;!-- error.html --&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;
      Uh oh, looks like something went wrong :/
    &lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Go ahead and upload these files to the bucket we just created. Make sure when you do, to select â€œGrant public read access to this object(s)â€.</p>

<p>To test our static site is serving the correct files, you can find the endpoint under your bucketâ€™s â€œPropertiesâ€ settings.
Find the URL located at â€œPropertiesâ€ -&gt; â€œStatic website hostingâ€.
Test that out in the browser and you should see the following content:
